Package: jocf
Title: Joint Ordered Correlation Forest
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Author", "Name", , "author@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Estimates conditional choice probabilities for ordered discrete
    outcomes using a single random forest with a joint splitting criterion
    that minimises average estimation error across all classes simultaneously.
    In contrast to the published 'ocf' package, which grows M separate
    forests, 'jocf' grows one forest whose splitting rule is equivalent to
    minimising total CART Gini impurity (Proposition 1 in the package vignette).
